      NFT Stuff
   =20
 =20
A basic theory that seems to explain a lot of crypto stuff is that a lot of=
 people got way too rich way too fast by buying crypto early, and now they =
are desperately trying to find the dumbest possible ways to get rid of thei=
r money.=C2=A0Or something:In the latest phase of the quest to turn everyth=
ing into an NFT, crypto traders are now bidding to digitally own a 1,784-lb=
. cube of tungsten in Willowbrook, Illinois. According to the terms of the =
sale, which will have the receipt posted to the blockchain for posterity, t=
he =E2=80=9Cowner=E2=80=9D can have one supervised visit to the cube per ye=
ar to touch or photograph it. =E2=80=A6=E2=80=9CSince we began selling the =
cube we have constantly asked ourselves, 'What is the right size?', and 'Wo=
uld anyone buy a bigger cube?' Only recently has anyone asked us, or have w=
e asked ourselves, 'What is the biggest cube we can make?' We have an answe=
r that creates a bit of a problem. The answer is 14" and 1,784 lbs (809 kg)=
. The problem is, what do with it if we make it. Shipping and receiving can=
 be a problem,=E2=80=9D=C2=A0the company wrote in a blog post.=C2=A0To get =
around the issues inherent in creating such a massively heavy object for sa=
le, Midwest Tungsten has put some restrictions on the sale of the cube, whi=
ch will be kept at the company=E2=80=99s HQ:=C2=A0=E2=80=9COne visit to see=
/photograph/touch the cube per calendar year will be allowed and scheduled =
with a Midwest Tungsten Service representative,=E2=80=9D the NFT listing re=
ads. =E2=80=9CSubsequent owners of the NFT cannot visit the cube in a year =
in which the cube has already been visited. The cube will not be available =
to view until 10 weeks after the first sale.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0The minimum bid =
is 47.74 ETH, currently equivalent to $201,295.23.=C2=A0Oh yeah? Well, I ha=
ppen to have a 28-inch tungsten cube weighing=C2=A014,000 pounds in my base=
ment. You can buy it from me =E2=80=94=C2=A0in NFT form of course =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0for 381.92 ETH. If you buy my cube you can never visit, see, touch or=
 photograph it; it is much too special to be seen or touched. The advantage=
, to you, is that you don=E2=80=99t need to travel to Willowbrook, Illinois=
. And you=E2=80=99ll own the NFT of a really big tungsten cube. When the pe=
rson who owns this 14=E2=80=9D tungsten cube that she can visit once a year=
 is like =E2=80=9CI own a big tungsten cube in Illinois=E2=80=9D you can be=
 like =E2=80=9Coh yeah well I own an even bigger tungsten cube in New York=
=E2=80=9D and she=E2=80=99ll be like =E2=80=9Cprove it=E2=80=9D and you=E2=
=80=99ll be like =E2=80=9Cyou prove it=E2=80=9D and then you=E2=80=99ll bot=
h pull up some blockchain addresses and I guess you=E2=80=99ll be satisfied=
, I don=E2=80=99t know, I don=E2=80=99t know why you=E2=80=99d be satisfied=
, I don=E2=80=99t know why any of this is anything.[6] Anyway right 28-inch=
 tungsten cube in my basement, let the bidding begin.
