n. As we  discussed yesterday, deposits can be problematic for flush-with-c=
ash large commercial banks. Goldman is historically an investment bank and =
still kind of building its deposits business, so it=E2=80=99s happy to take=
 some of those deposits from the commercial banks.[3] It is perhaps a littl=
e fun to read the representations that TMTG makes, which are all fairly sta=
ndard but some of which feel =E2=80=A6=C2=A0un-Trumpy? =E2=80=9CNo Target C=
ompany, nor any of their respective Representatives acting on their behalf =
has (i)=C2=A0used any funds for unlawful contributions, gifts, entertainmen=
t or other unlawful expenses relating to political activity, (ii)=C2=A0made=
 any unlawful payment to foreign or domestic government officials or employ=
ees, to foreign or domestic political parties or campaigns or violated any =
provision of the U.S. Foreign Corrupt Practices Act of 1977 or any other lo=
cal or foreign anti-corruption or bribery Law or (iii)=C2=A0made any other =
unlawful payment,=E2=80=9D says Section 4.25(a). Trump does not like these =
rules! But I guess TMTG follows them.=C2=A0[4] There are 28.75 million publ=
ic shares and 7.2 million founder shares, per the DWAC prospectus. (Some of=
 the founder shares are allocated to hedge funds, not the actual DWAC spons=
or, as we  discussed on Monday.) The basic merger consideration for TMTG=E2=
=80=99s shareholders is $875 million divided by the redemption price of DWA=
C shares; DWAC appears to have about $10.20 per share in its trust, so that=
 number is about 85.8 million shares.=C2=A0[5] Specifically, if the volume =
weighted average price of the stock is above $15 for 20 out of any 30 tradi=
ng days during the 18 months after closing, Trump et al. get an extra 15 mi=
llion shares; if it=E2=80=99s above $20 during the two years after closing,=
 they get another 15=C2=A0million; if it=E2=80=99s above $30 during the thr=
ee years after closing, they get another 10 million. See Section 1.17 of th=
e merger agreement.[6] Ugh, fine, their cube seems to have a physical deliv=
ery option? =E2=80=9CAccording to the listing, the only way to take physica=
l possession of the cube will be to burn the NFT, meaning send it to a dead=
-end address so it can no longer be traded.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0 I assume no one =
will ever exercise that option, because =E2=80=9Ctransferable NFT entitleme=
nt to a tungsten cube that you can trade on the blockchain and that can at =
your option be turned into a real tungsten cube=E2=80=9D is more valuable t=
han just a tungsten cube; why exercise and lose the optionality value?=C2=
